llows%20a%20pair%20of%20wireless%20earbuds%20or%20headphones%20to%20simultaneously%20connect%20to%20two%20source%20devices%2C%20like%20a%20phone%20and%20a%20computer.%20While%20you%20obviously%20won't%20be%20playing%20audio%20from%20both%20devices%20at%20once%2C%20multipoint%20pairing%20makes%20it%20easy%20to%20swap%20between%20the%20two%2C%20so%20you%20can%20take%20a%20call%20on%20your%20phone%2C%20jump%20into%20a%20Zoom%20meeting%20on%20your%20computer%2C%20and%20listen%20to%20audio%20from%20either%20device%20without%20the%20need%20to%20connect%20and%20disconnect%20your%20earbuds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20noise-canceling%20and%20transparency%20modes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENoise-canceling%20and%20transparency%20modes%20are%20both%20considered%20%26quot%3Bambient%20sound%26quot%3B%20modes%2C%20which%20use%20exterior%20microphones%20and%20advanced%20sound%20processing.%20But%20they're%20essentially%20the%20exact%20opposite%20of%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EActive%20noise%20canceling%20(ANC)%20uses%20algorithms%20that%20constantly%20monitor%20environmental%20frequencies%20and%20then%20flip%20their%20polarity%20before%20being%20piped%20into%20your%20ears.%20This%20reversal%20of%20the%20sine%20wave%20of%20each%20frequency%20affected%20will%20%26quot%3Bcancel%26quot%3B%20the%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20transparency%20mode%20is%20designed%20to%20let%20in%20environmental%20sounds%2C%20letting%20you%20stay%20aware%20of%20your%20surroundings%20while%20still%20using%20earbuds%20or%20headphones.%20There's%20still%20advanced%20sound%20processing%20happening%20with%20transparency%20mode%2C%20however.%20You%20can%20usually%20increase%20or%20decrease%20the%20volume%20level%2C%20and%20the%20best%20versions%20from%20brands%20like%20Bose%20and%20Apple%20can%20even%20employ%20audio%20compression%20that%20attempts%20to%20block%20and%2For%20reduce%20sudden%20loud%20noises%20to%20protect%20your%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20our%20top%20recommendations%20that%20feature%20these%20modes%2C%20check%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-noise-cancelling-headphones%5C%22%3Ebest%20noise-canceling%20headphones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20spatial%20audio%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESpatial%20audio%2C%20as%20it%20applies%20specifically%20to%20earbuds%20and%20headphones%2C%20is%20a%20feature%20that%20uses%20virtualization%20to%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20three-dimensional%20space%20and%20depth%20from%20just%20two%20speakers.%20Multiple%20versions%20are%20available%2C%20though%20Apple's%20is%20the%20best%20we've%20tried%20so%20far%20when%20using%20Dolby%20Atmos%20mixes%20as%20a%20source%2C%20creating%20a%20more%20authentic%20sense%20of%20immersion.%20While%20many%20spatial%20audio%20implementations%20also%20work%20with%20stereo%20sources%2C%20we%20think%20this%20is%20generally%20less%20effective%20than%20using%20the%20feature%20in%20conjunction%20with%203D%20audio%20formats%20like%20Atmos.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20versions%20of%20spatial%20audio%20also%20use%20head%20tracking%2C%20which%20is%20designed%20to%20create%20a%20sonic%20environment%20more%20like%20listening%20to%20regular%20speakers.%20For%20example%2C%20with%20head%20tracking%20engaged%2C%20turning%20your%20head%20with%20your%20earbuds%20on%20causes%20the%20soundstage%20to%20remain%20centered%2C%20as%20though%20you're%20turning%20your%20head%20from%20a%20real%20pair%20of%20speakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpatial%20audio%20is%20becoming%20more%20common%20for%20music%2C%20with%20engineers%20increasingly%20focusing%20on%20mixing%20songs%20for%20a%203D%20environment.%20That%20said%2C%20in%20our%20opinion%2C%20spatial%20audio%20is%20still%20most%20effective%20for%20video%20content%20like%20movies%20and%20TV%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider