n%20Revolution%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20only%20hybrid%20seeds%20were%20to%20be%20supplied%20to%20the%20market%20to%20the%20farmers.%20This%20was%20never%20a%20solution%20for%20an%20%E2%80%98evergreen%E2%80%99%20revolution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20opines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20hybrid%20seeds%20offer%20higher%20yields%20in%20one%20season%2C%20they%20cannot%20be%20saved%20for%20the%20following%20year.%20Consequently%2C%20farmers%20neglected%20heirloom%20seeds%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20their%20sovereignty%20over%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%20Since%20then%2C%20Neelam%E2%80%99s%20mission%20has%20been%20to%20conserve%20decade-old%20seeds%20for%20future%20generations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20the%20traditional%20wisdom%20imparted%20by%20his%20father%20and%20the%20elderly%20in%20the%20village%2C%20he%20set%20out%20in%20search%20of%20these%20heirloom%20treasures.%20In%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20Neelam%20has%20conserved%20nearly%20800%20varieties%20of%20vegetables%20like%20tomatoes%2C%20chillies%2C%20capsicum%2C%20basil%2C%20and%20200%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331636%2Fassam-farmer-starts-rice-library-grows-preserves-indigenous-rice-varieties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evarieties%20of%20rice%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Cem%3Emadhuri%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Enanyya%20rice%2C%20sticky%20gum%20rice%2C%20black%20rice%2C%20soft%20rice%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejoha.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20seeds%20have%20their%20own%20identity%20in%20terms%20of%20taste%2C%20colour%2C%20and%20shape.%20They%20are%20adaptable%20to%20the%20diverse%20Indian%20climatic%20zones.%20In%20one%20way%2C%20they%20are%20more%20resilient%20than%20hybrid%20seeds%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHybrid%20vs%20heirloom%20seeds%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigur